'''''eLife'''''是一个[[生物医学|生物医学]]及[[生命科学|生命科学]]方向的需要[[同行评审|同行评审]]的[[开放获取|开放获取]]的[[科学期刊|科学期刊]]。2010年，在一次[[霍华德·休斯医学研究所|霍华德·休斯医学研究所]][[珍利亚农场研究园区|珍利亚农场研究园区]]举办的[[学术研讨会|学术研讨会]]后，由[[霍华德·休斯医学研究所|霍华德·休斯医学研究所]]、[[马克斯·普朗克学会|马克斯·普朗克学会]]，以及[[惠康基金会|惠康基金会]]决定共同赞助创办。该期刊正式创立于2012年底。<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.wellcome.ac.uk/About-us/Policy/Spotlight-issues/Open-access/Journal/index.htm |title="eLife", a new open access journal |publisher=[[Wellcome_Trust|Wellcome Trust]] |accessdate=10 April 2012 |archive-date=2014-07-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140702164148/http://www.wellcome.ac.uk/About-us/Policy/Spotlight-issues/Open-access/Journal/index.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="#1">{{citation |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-17668722 |date=10 April 2012 |title=Trust pushes for open access to research |author=Matt McGrath |publisher=[[BBC|BBC]] |accessdate=2014-08-07 |archive-date=2015-04-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150416062808/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-17668722 |dead-url=no }}</ref> 第一年该杂志共发表287篇文章。<ref>Looked up via the journal's browse page on 21 Oct 2013.</ref>这些组织共同提供了初始资金来支持商业和出版业务<ref name="#1"/>，并且在2016年，这些组织承诺投入2600万美元继续出版该期刊<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Callaway |first=Ewen |date=2016-06-02 |title=Open-access journal eLife gets £25-million boost |url=http://www.nature.com/news/open-access-journal-elife-gets-25-million-boost-1.20005 |journal=[[Nature_(journal)|Nature]] |volume=534 |issue=7605 |pages=14–15 |doi=10.1038/534014a |access-date=2018-04-14 |archive-date=2017-10-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171002002425/http://www.nature.com/news/open-access-journal-elife-gets-25-million-boost-1.20005 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

[[主编|主编]]是[[兰迪·谢克曼|兰迪·谢克曼]]（[[加州大学伯克利分校|加州大学伯克利分校]]）<ref name=THE>{{citation |url=http://www.timeshighereducation.co.uk/story.asp?sectioncode=26&storycode=418047&c=1 |title=Open-access science journal leaves editing to the experts |date=5 November 2011 |author=Freya Boardman-Pretty |journal=[[Times_Higher_Education|Times Higher Education]] |accessdate=2014-08-07 |archive-date=2011-11-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111115151057/http://www.timeshighereducation.co.uk/story.asp?sectioncode=26&storycode=418047&c=1 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。编辑决策主要由高级编辑和审稿编辑委员会成员完成，他们都是在{{link-en|人类遗传学|Human genetics}}和[[神经科学|神经科学]]到[[生物物理|生物物理]]和[[流行病学|流行病学]]领域工作的活跃科学家<ref>{{citation |url=http://elifesciences.org/about |title=Communicating the latest advances in life science and biomedicine |publisher=eLife |accessdate=6 October 2015 |archive-date=2018-04-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180405205501/https://elifesciences.org/about |dead-url=no }}</ref> 。

== 商业模式 ==
eLife是一家[[非营利组织|非营利组织]]，但为了服务的长期可持续性，该期刊要求对接受发表的论文收取$3,000美元的[[版面费|版面费]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://elifesciences.org/elife-news/inside-elife-setting-fee-publication |title=Inside eLife: Setting a fee for publication |access-date=2016-09-29|date=2016-09-29 }}</ref>。 资金不足的作者有资格获得费用减免。

== 文摘和索引 ==
该杂志在[[Medline|Medline]]，[[生物学文摘（预评）数据库|生物学文摘（预评）数据库]](BIOSIS Previews)<ref name=ISI>{{cite web |url=http://ip-science.thomsonreuters.com/mjl/ |title=Master Journal List |publisher=[[Thomson_Reuters|Thomson Reuters]] |work=Intellectual Property & Science |accessdate=2016-10-10 |archive-date=2011-12-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111221082940/http://ip-science.thomsonreuters.com/mjl/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>， [[化学文摘社|化学文摘社]]<ref name=CASSI>{{cite web |url=http://cassi.cas.org/search.jsp |archive-url=https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20100211181038/http://cassi.cas.org/search.jsp |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2010-02-11 |title=CAS Source Index |publisher=[[American_Chemical_Society|American Chemical Society]] |work=[[Chemical_Abstracts_Service|Chemical Abstracts Service]] |accessdate=2016-10-10 |df= }}</ref>，[[科学引文索引|科学引文索引]]<ref name=ISI/>和[[斯高帕斯数据库|斯高帕斯数据库(Scopus)]] <ref name=Scopus>{{cite web |url=http://www.elsevier.com/online-tools/scopus/content-overview |title=Content overview |publisher=[[Elsevier|Elsevier]] |work=Scopus |accessdate=2016-10-10 |archive-date=2015-04-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150424035942/http://www.elsevier.com/online-tools/scopus/content-overview |dead-url=no }}</ref>中被做文摘和索引。 根据期刊引用报告，该杂志的2016年影响因子为7.725 <ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2016 |chapter=eLife |title=2015 [[Journal_Citation_Reports|Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson_Reuters|Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Science |series=[[Web_of_Science|Web of Science]]}}</ref>（2013年为8.52，2014年为9.32，2015年为8.28）。 该杂志称其不会促进其影响因子<ref>{{citation |url=http://elifesciences.org/about |title=Communicating the latest advances in life science and biomedicine |publisher=eLife |accessdate=26 October 2015 |archive-date=2018-04-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180405205501/https://elifesciences.org/about |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在接受采访时，霍华德休斯医学研究院院长[[錢澤南|錢澤南]]对《eLife》进行了回顾，并指出：「我們試著不讓那些統計的人也來計算我們的影響指數。他們無論如何都提早一年給我們影響指數，別問我這是什麼情況，因為我真的不想知道，也不在乎。」<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://news.sciencemag.org/funding/2015/08/qa-outgoing-hhmi-chief-reflects-leading-18-billion-biomedical-charity |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2018-04-14 |archive-date=2015-11-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151104171121/http://news.sciencemag.org/funding/2015/08/qa-outgoing-hhmi-chief-reflects-leading-18-billion-biomedical-charity |dead-url=no }}</ref>

